{
  "texts": [
    "By leveraging an existing DDR1 inhibitory molecular scaffold, they generated 30,000 structures adjusting the substituent groups of this scaffold to enhance its pharmacological efficacy which were then computationally screened.",
    "From this, six were synthesized based on their synthetic feasibility and target profile.",
    "Two showcased potent inhibitory and pharmacokinetic properties.",
    "In 2022, Xiaoqin et al.",
    "(24) also utilized deep learning to design selective inhibitors for DDR1 using a generative scaffold decorator."
  ]
}